In effect, this part of the budget will really amount to extra tax employees to harass people who are employess all of their lives, and are late on their taxes, that is all. 
An authoritarian response to a failed economic plan. The government has no idea what they are doing, or how to get out of the hole they are digging. They are having a REVENUE CRISIS, because they have no ideas how to spur anything. This government thinks a successful economy can be based on , taking money from me, and giving it to Juanita and Farsi to spend, in the name of Child Benefit cheques. 
So, they will harass a few bucks out of already overtaxed employees in response to their abysmal failure, and tax cigs and alcohol more, because Johnny Lunchpail still has a few bucks left over for a night of relaxation once in a while. Disgusting, stupid socialist authoritarian garbage, not a budget at all.
Give me Trumps tax cuts, give me the US's tax rate, give me the US's cig and alcohol tax rate, give me the price of food and housing in the US. Canada is failing.

In effect, this part of the budget will really amount to extra tax employees to harass people who are employess all of their lives, and are late on their taxes, that is all. 
An authoritarian response to a failed economic plan. The government has no idea what they are doing, or how to get out of the hole they are digging. They are having a REVENUE CRISIS, because they have no ideas how to spur anything. This government thinks a successful economy can be based on , taking money from me, and giving it to Juanita and Farsi to spend, in the name of Child Benefit cheques. 
So, they will harass a few bucks out of already overtaxed employees in response to their abysmal failure, and tax cigs and alcohol more, because Johnny Lunchpail still has a few bucks left over for a night of relaxation once in a while. Disgusting, stupid socialist authoritarian garbage, not a budget at all.
Give me Trumps tax cuts, give me the US's tax rate, give me the US's cig and alcohol tax rate, give me the price of food and housing in the US. Canada is failing.

text_original_comment:
Canada is 150 years old. Happy Birthday Canada..............

150 years of murder, oppression, assimilation and genocide towards the indigenous tribes and native peoples that already resided here LONG before it became a country. 

This country was founded on lies & betrayal. ðŸ’¯ 
There is an ugly part of our history that must not be swept under the rug.  

At least 6,000 indigenous children died while in the residential school system.

Residential schools were established in the 19th century as a colonial strategy to "take the Indian out of the child" and destroy indigenous cultures.  It was nothing short of an attempt at cultural genocide.  The last schools didn't close until 1996. 

The legacy of the abuse experienced by these innocent children in Canada's residential schools is extensive. Over the century that they operated, indigenous children aged five to 16 were forcibly taken away from their families and subjected to horrific psychological, physical, spiritual and sexual abuse, leaving a legacy of dysfunction that has been passed down to the second and third generations.  Some children who attended the schools in the 1940s and 1950s were even subjected to science experiments in which they were deprived essential nutrients and dental care.  

The first step is for all Canadians to understand what happened and what the schools did to indigenous peoples.  The second step is committing that we will support action to ensure the repair of damages done. 
Social, Economic and Environmental Terrorism being perpetrated upon the Original Peoples of this land is the ongoing agenda of the colonial governments regardless of their political ideologies in the political spectrum.

comment_message_cleaned: Unfortunately, there is no federal law that governs scanner price accuracy. However, many retailers uphold the Scanner Price Accuracy Voluntary Code which is endorsed by the Competition Bureau of Canada. The code includes the Item Free Scanner Policy which stipulates: if an item scanned at checkout is a higher price than advertised by the store or displayed in the store, the lower price will be honoured. Also, if the correct price of the product is $10 or less, the retailer will give the product to the customer free of charge; or, if the product is over $10, the retailer will give a discount of $10 off the correct price. The next time this happens to you, ask if the retailer upholds the code. You can learn more about the Scanner Price Accuracy Voluntary Code here: [[SHARE]]

Unfortunately, there is no federal law that governs scanner price accuracy. However, many retailers uphold the Scanner Price Accuracy Voluntary Code which is endorsed by the Competition Bureau of Canada. The code includes the Item Free Scanner Policy which stipulates: if an item scanned at checkout is a higher price than advertised by the store or displayed in the store, the lower price will be honoured.
